With Rob Morrow (Numb3rs) and John Turturro, directed by Robert Redford.

Mesmerising, true quality drama about the American celebrity hero who in 1958 confessed publicly that the popular television quiz shows were fixed. 

Only full DVDs remain here on PirateBay. I started to make a new rip, but found this torrent on another site and checked it out. Great picture quality and sound.

Note: The original English soundtrack is #2. Most players on the computer allow choise of soundtrack with right-click. On your standalone DivX player, you use the remote as for a DVD. ConvertXtoDVD will include both sound tracks.

Widescreen 624x336, good stereo.
Burn tested, runs well in my DivX player.
